Script to fit Biomass model from Urban trees in Santiago. Full code can be view at [github.com/spalmas/Santiago](https://github.com/spalmas/Santiago)

####Load Packages
```{r}
require(xlsx)
```

####Get Data
```{r}
#Set working directory
setwd("~/Google Drive/Urban")

arboles <- read.xlsx(file="arboles_2002-2014.xlsx", sheetName = 'Parcelas con arboles')
spp.both <- read.xlsx(file="arboles_2002-2014.xlsx", sheetName = 'Spp in both yrs')
FieldLandUses <- read.xlsx(file="FieldLandUses.xlsx", sheetName = 'FieldLandUses')
GroundCovers <- read.xlsx(file="PlotGrndCvr.xlsx", sheetName = 'GroundCovers')
GroundCoverType <- read.xlsx(file="PlotGrndCvr.xlsx", sheetName = 'GroundCoverType')
Plots <- read.xlsx(file="PlotLandUSe.xlsx", sheetName = 'Plots')
LandUseID <- read.xlsx(file="PlotLandUSe.xlsx", sheetName = 'LandUseID')
Shrubs <- read.xlsx(file="Shrubs.xlsx", sheetName = 'Shrubs')
Trees <- read.xlsx(file="TreeBiometrics.xlsx", sheetName = 'Trees')
Subplots <- read.xlsx(file="TreeShrbCvr.xlsx", sheetName = 'Subplots')
```

####Structure 
```{r}
str(arboles)
```
